> Salsa fresca is our favorite way to feel warm weather vibes all year round. It's juicy and tangy with a touch of heat, making it the perfect complement to crispy, turmeric-and-cumin-spiced barramundi. The fillets are served on top of steamy yellow rice and blanketed in lime crema and said salsa. No matter the temperature, one bite of this delicious dish will make everything feel a whole lot sunnier.

== Salsa Fresca ==

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Mince @chili pepper{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomatoes, cilantro, juice from half the lime, and scallion whites. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. If you like spicy salsa, stir in chili to taste.

== Yellow Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the scallion whites and @turmeric{1/4%tsp} (add 1/4 tsp for 2 servings, 1/2 tsp for 4); cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. (You'll use more turmeric later.)

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Zesty Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, a big squeeze of lime juice, and as much lime zest as you like. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Barramundi ==

In a #second small bowl{}, combine @cumin{1%tsp} and @turmeric{1/4%tsp} (add 1/4 tsp for 2 servings, 1/2 tsp for 4). (Be sure to measure the turmeric.)

Pat @barramundi{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Season flesh sides with spice mixture.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add barramundi, skin sides down, and cook until skin is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in scallion greens and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between plates; top with barramundi. Garnish with salsa fresca and crema and serve.